meta.objective: visualize the noise inside my head

SON.context: Collection of images that provide inspiration
SON.painless-definition: The sensation caused by vibrating wave motion that is perceived by the organs of hearing | (not painless)

ECH.painless-definition: A reflected sound that is heard again by its initial observer

TIM.painless-definition: The quality of a sound independent of its pitch and volume

RES.painless-definition: Something that evokes an association, or a strong emotion

WAV.painless-definition: The shape of a physical wave, such as sound, electric current or electromagnetic radiation, or its representation obtained by plotting a characteristic of the phenomenon versus another variable, often time.

SYN.painless-definition: To stress or accentuate the weak beat of a rhythm

LYR.painless-definition: The words of a song or other vocal music. The singular form often refers to a part of the words, whereas the plural form can refer to all of the words

FRE.painless-definition: Number of times an event occurred in an experiment

OCT.painless-definition: An interval of twelve semitones spanning eight degrees of the diatonic scale, representing a doubling or halving in pitch frequency

CAN.painless-definition: A chant, hymn or song, especially a nonmetrical one, with words from a biblical text
